## Verdict
PARTIAL

## Boundary integration
- [x] Pure substrate (no live HTTP)
- [ ] Workspace-scoped
- [ ] on_fetcher_error semantics correct
- [x] Duplicate URL dedup correct

## New findings (if any)
[MEDIUM] `src/polaris_graph/audit_ir/cache_warming.py:235` — `workspace_id` is not validated as `str`. Non-string inputs either leak an `AttributeError` (`123`) or, for `b"ws1"`, silently succeed and warm a cache namespace that normal `"ws1"` lookups cannot see. That violates the public API and can create effectively orphaned warmed entries.

[MEDIUM] `src/polaris_graph/audit_ir/cache_warming.py:244` — fetcher validation only checks `hasattr(fetcher, "fetch")`. A fetcher with a non-callable `fetch` attribute is accepted, and in default `on_fetcher_error="record"` mode the resulting `TypeError` is recorded as a per-URL fetch failure instead of surfacing as a fetcher contract error.

## Final word
PARTIAL until `workspace_id` is enforced as `str` and `fetcher.fetch` is validated as callable or otherwise treated as a contract error.

Scoped `pytest` could not complete in this sandbox because `pytest` tempdir setup/cleanup hits `WinError 5`; the findings above were confirmed with targeted local repros.
